Lebanon Takes in About 1,000 Refugees From Syria, Guardian Says

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-06-25T10:28:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/lebanon-takes-in-about-1-000-refugees-from-syria-guardian-says.html
As many as 1,000 Syrians fled to
neighboring Lebanon after 20 people were killed in anti-
government protests yesterday, the Guardian  reported today ,
citing an unnamed Lebanese security official.  The refugees escaped via the al-Qusair crossing into
northern Lebanon, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in Abu Dhabi at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  